  "texts": [
    "All components are open source software, which means the repository can easily be cloned and adapted to the needs of different researchers, labs, institutions, and societies (see gitlab.com/psy-ops/PsyCoRe.one).",
    "PsyCoRe also creates unique URLs using the UCID of each included DCT specification, allowing unequivocal reference to construct definitions.",
    "These URLs show the construct's UCID, label, definition, and the four sets of instructions.",
    "It also links to the DCT specification's YAML file on GitLab, allowing researchers to easily download it (and then, for example, adjust it and upload the adjusted version, which will then obtain a unique UCID).",
    "In addition to creating a webpage for each DCT specification, PsyCoRe also creates a number of overviews: a searchable table showing all constructs and which instructions are available for each as well as overviews with all definitions and an overview for each type of instruction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}